I"ê<blockquote>
  <p><strong>Note</strong>: The <code class="highlighter-rouge">dtrace</code> security restrcition needs to be disabled on <em>El Capitan</em>. Boot into recovery mode â†’ <code class="highlighter-rouge">csrutil enable --without dtrace</code>.</p>
</blockquote>

<h2 id="capture-stdout">Capture stdout</h2>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>dtrace <span class="nt">-p</span> &lt;<span class="nv">$PID</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="nt">-qn</span> <span class="s1">'syscall::write*:entry /pid == $target &amp;&amp; arg0 == 1/ { printf("%s", copyinstr(arg1, arg2)); }'</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="capture-stderr">Capture stderr</h2>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>dtrace <span class="nt">-p</span> &lt;<span class="nv">$PID</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="nt">-qn</span> <span class="s1">'syscall::write*:entry /pid == $target &amp;&amp; arg0 == 2/ { printf("%s", copyinstr(arg1, arg2)); }'</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="capture-both">Capture both</h2>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>dtrace <span class="nt">-p</span> &lt;<span class="nv">$PID</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="nt">-qn</span> <span class="s1">'syscall::write*:entry /pid == $target &amp;&amp; (arg0 == 1 || arg0 == 2)/ { printf("%s", copyinstr(arg1, arg2)); }'</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

